snippet: Government troops on Friday raided a house in Mogadishu belonging to a former warlord as part of a disarmament campaign, setting off a clash that left at least seven people dead.
abstract: Somali government troops raid house in Mogadishu belonging to former warlord Ahmed Daci as part of a disarmament campaign, setting off clash that leaves at least seven people dead.
lead_paragraph: Government troops on Friday raided a house in Mogadishu belonging to a former warlord as part of a disarmament campaign, setting off a clash that left at least seven people dead.

headline.main: Somalia: Troops Seize Weapons in Raid
